description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you currently working with children and looking for a new role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Would you like to progress your career by working with children who require complex clinical care?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare is seeking experienced Health Care Assistants to support a young girl with complex care needs. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;We are looking for dedicated and compassionate Health Care Assistants who are passionate about their job, enjoy delivering one to one support and who can build positive relationships with our service users and their families.  &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Our service user is a young girl who lives with her family in the Grange-over-sands area.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;She requires support throughout the night to ensure she remains safe and well. She can wake during the night so may require comforting by way of gentle reassurance and bedtime stories.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;She loves bedtime stories and likes when her carers speak to her even though she is nonverbal. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Our ideal candidate will be diligent, confident &amp; have a genuine interest for working with children. You must be able to evidence this in your application. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;* 6 months previous care experience  &lt;br /&gt;* Medication Administration  &lt;br /&gt;* Personal Care  &lt;br /&gt;* Moving and Handling  &lt;br /&gt;* Drivers required due to location&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;* Cognitive brain condition&lt;br /&gt;* Jejunostomy&lt;br /&gt;* Mickey Button (Peg feeding)&lt;br /&gt;* Respiratory assessment experience&lt;br /&gt;* Nebuliser&lt;br /&gt;* Oral Suctioning&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;* Night shifts available from 9pm – 7am&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;   &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on her day to day life. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why work for Apollo Home Healthcare?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We specialise in the provision of highly complex clinical care services delivered in the homes of service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about delivering the highest standard of care and we recognise that our Nurses, Healthcare Assistants and Support Workers are integral to doing this. In return for your hard work and dedication you will receive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours to suit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirmed rotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent rates of pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full clinical training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work with other service users in the area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing professional training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need key workers on the front line supporting our service users in the fight against the COVID-19 Pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
